              <tr><td colspan="3">    <table width="600" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
    <tr><td width="200" valign="top"><b>Bullsmasher</b><br>
LORE ITEM <br>
Skill: 1HB&nbsp;&nbsp;Atk Delay: 20<br>
DMG: 6<br>
+2 STR, +2 DEX, +2 AGI<br>
WT: 4.0<br>
Class: WAR, CLR, PAL, RNG, SHD, SHM<br>
Race: DWF, HFL, GNM</td>
    
    <td width="100" align="center" valign="top">
    <b>Item Icon</b><br>
    None Available</td>

    <td width="150" valign="top">
    <b>Obtained From</b><br>
    Quest<br>
Level 5</td>
    <td width="150" valign="top">
    <b>Additional Info</b><br>
    Type: Weapon, 1HB<br>
Damage Per Second: 6.5<br>
Zone(s): akanon<br>
Last Updated: 04/16/00<br>
</td></tr>
    </table>
    <br><br>
    <b>Description</b><br>
If you complete a quest given by Drekon who lives in Ak'Anon, he sometimes will give you this second quest.  Drekon talks about the rumors that Red V must be alive.  He wants you to bring him back Red V's blackbox and give it to Manik. 
<br><br>
Off to the Mines of Malfunction in Ak'Anon, head to the South-Eastern most room.  Just keep killing the spawns until Red V pops.  Kill Red V and he will drop an incomplete blackbox.  To fix this blackbox, kill tons of the Obsolete Models that also wander the mines, they drop blackbox fragments.  Collect four of these fragments, put them in the incomplete blackbox and hit combine, and you will be left with a Rusted Blackbox.  Hand the rusted blackbox to Manik and he will reward you, sometimes even with a nice item, such as the Bullsmasher, or Iony's Absorber.  <br><br>
<b>Player Comments</b> (total:4, showing:1-4) <a href="JavaScript:popComment('comment.php3?type=item&tid=61')">add</a><br>
<a href="mailto:ericdee@home.com">gnebin</a> of the tarew marr server on Feb. 21, 2000 at 05:39pm said...<br>
red 5 does not spawn every 2 hours. he has a place holder that spawns every 5 min. red is random in that spot. i have seen him spawn 3 times in 20min. also, you dont need to be considered kindly by the gemchoppers. i know i wasnt when i completed this quest. something else that makes me angry is the public view of this fine weapon. i see this item sold for 250pp on tarew marr (once and a while. ive only seen it in auction a few times), while the crystalline blade nears 1k. i dont get it. the smasher has a better dmg ratio, and modifiers. only thing i can think of, is that it is not magic (which seems stupid since it has modifers). so what though. how often do you fight magic creatures? i just carry around a backup magic weapon. im lvl 32 and still use this weapon as a secondary to my painbringer (both are very close in dmg ratios). anyhoo, this can be a long and non productive quest (unless you like patchwork), but it is worth it!  =)<br><br>
<a href="mailto:sbutcher@alltel.net">Blackened</a> of the Emarr server on Feb. 14, 2000 at 08:00am said...<br>
I completed this quest yesterday.  It is not as easy as people might think.  I first suggest that you con the NPC Manik Comptein(sp).  Wait until he kindly regards you before wasting your time.  I gained faction by killin Minos for several hours.  I think I killed about 30 or more.  Once he regards you as kindly, kill 8 Runaway Clockworks.  Collect the fragments and head down to find Red V.  The spot where he spawns will produce a Spawn every 2hours Game Time.  Red 5 doesn't always spawn but something will. (Obsolete models). The first time Red 5 spawns, kill him and get the box.  Put 4 blackbox fragments in it and hit combine.  This will now fit into a back pack spot.  I suggest to wait for another spawn of Red 5.  Once he spawns again, kill him.  Get the box but dont hit combine yet(you cannot have two of the same item).  Go turn the completed box into Manik Compotein(sp).  If he doesn't give you the bullsmasher, con him and make sure he look at you KINDLY.  Combine the other parts and give him another competed box or go kill some more Minos then come back.  I really like the weapon.  It is a very nice 1hblunt weapon.  I can now carry a shield.  My next quest is the Staff of the Observer.  I have obtained the quest but have be waiting to kill the Evil Eye for quite some time now.  30ish mob and Im only 15.  Good luck to you!!
Blackened
<br><br>
<a href="mailto:porkyhead@netzero.net">Alater</a> of the E'ci server on Jan. 31, 2000 at 05:14pm said...<br>
The bullsmasher says it can be wielded by Rangers...However the race restriction doesnt make sense...Only Gnomes, Dwarves and Haflings can use it...I've never seen a Gnome Ranger have you? hehe  If anyone knows if a Ranger can use this nice little mace post away...<br><br>
<a href="mailto:emperorstarfire@hotmail.com">Ceratul</a> of the Cazic-Thule server on Nov. 08, 1999 at 02:09am said...<br>
this item comes from a quest in ak'anon, you kill red v, a rogue clock work, and get an incomplete blackbox, then you kill the placeholders, and get blackbox fragments, combine them in the incomplete blackbox, turn in at the warriors guild, and sometimes you will recieve the bullsmasher. Red V spawns in the necro guild. you MUST be a small race to be able to fight red V, because of the height of the tunnels<br><br>
